review_blob:
Nice golden/amber appearance. Definitaly inticed me a bit.
 Head was a nice tan color.Left a nice ring around my glass. Very tasty. Real toasty malt, caramel, very smooth. Did have a slight aftertaste. But not bad enough to change my mind overall. I enjoyed it and would enjoy drinking it again

I pretty much agree with johndo2000. Last time I visited the brew we also went to the pub. I tried it for the first time and was happy and disappointed. Happy that I was drinking a good beer from my state, and sad that I'd have to drive all the way from Houma to drink it again
Flavor does beat the aroma. Very little wheat taste. Its a seasonal beer and this year taste better than last years. Overall not bad. Its worth the price.
